name: Mountains in Monochrome by Bondhu Dey

metadata.name: A Regal Scene
metadata.description: Here, you can see the regal Mt.Kanchenjunga range. Mount Kanchenjunga is the third highest peak in the world, and the 2nd highest in the Himalayas at a mammoth 8586 meters above the sea level, it is one of the most fantastic sights in the world. Seen from the Northeastern state of Sikkim, its grandeur and picturesque aura boggles your mind and makes you fall in awe of Mother Nature. Climbing this mountain is restricted from some areas, as it is considered holy. The highest mountain peak in India, it is one of the many treasures that lie in this beautiful country.
